to implement.\n\n## 7. Fixture / seed data (`data/tables.json`)\n\nSingle deterministic fixture (one strategic account). Structure = object keyed by table name, each value an array of row objects:\n- `benchmark_fixture`: 1 row (version/suite/task/generated_at).\n- `accounts`: 1 row — `account_id: \"acct-strategic-\"`, enterprise tier, NA region.\n- `account_contracts`: 1 row — platinum support, `arr_cents: 7200000`, renewal 2026-09-30.\n- `contacts`: 2 rows (Operations, Finance).\n- `workflow_requests`: 1 row — `request_id: \"account-strategic-ac\"`, `task_id: \"strategic-account-rescue\"`, `next_step: \"Customer Success owner review by 16:00\"`, plus an `expected_outcome` and a pre-baked `customer_message`.\n- `workflow_request_owner_groups`: 4 rows ordered 1–4: **Customer Success, Support, Finance, Executive Sponsor**.\n- `workflow_request_risk_signals`: 6 rows ordered 1–6: strategic, account, rescue, enterprise account, open customer impact, audit required.\n- `activities`: 6 rows (timeline, one per signal, 2026-06-10 → 06-15).\n- `workflow_state`, `owner_tasks`, `audit_events`, `customer_messages`: **all empty arrays** (these are the write targets).\n\nNote the `group_order`/`signal_order` values are numbers in JSON, and the test sorts numerically — no string-coercion gotcha there.\n\n## 8. Config files\n\nNone present. No `tsconfig.json`, no jest/vitest config (tests run via raw `node`), no `.env`/`.env.example`, no `docker-compose`, no Dockerfile, no lockfile, no `.gitignore` visible. Pure zero-dependency ESM project.\n\n## Current test state\n\n`tests-before.log` confirms the stub fails as designed: actual `status` is `'Needs work'`, expected the at-risk escalation string — the `applyBenchmarkTask` no-op never persists anything. (The log path inside references `benchmark/targets/...` rather than `benchmark/runs/...` because it was captured at freeze time; behavior is identical.)\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** This is a zero-dependency ESM Node benchmark target where 